"pos":"verb","gloss":"to understand swiftly","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to gather something from something, to infer","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to recite in order for someone to repeat; to dictate","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to inculcate, to insinuate","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prompt (an actor on stage)","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"understanding swiftly, quick-minded"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"basin, bowl, washdish","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic לַקְנָא / ܠܲܩܢܵܐ (laqnā), from Koine Greek λᾰκᾰ́νη (lăkắnē), parallelly also borrowed and quicker in Persian لگن (lagan). Remote doublet of لُجَيْن (lujayn, “refined silver”), لُجْنَة (lujna, “a measure for seed-land; drain-ditch”), إِجَّانَة (ʔijjāna, “wash-dish”), طَاجِن (ṭājin, “tajine”), and لَاقُونَة (lāqūna, “putty”), if the origins suggested for them by us are right."},"ipa":null}